Title: Unauthorized Access and Privilege Escalation Detected

Description:
Multiple failed login attempts were detected from IP address 192.168.1.100, targeting several user accounts (root, admin, user). A successful login to the admin account was later observed from the same IP address. After gaining access, the attacker escalated privileges from admin to root.

Additionally, another suspicious IP address 10.0.0.45 showed repeated failed login attempts. A user also reported entering their credentials on a phishing email sent from support@secure-login.com, indicating a possible credential compromise.

Initial Assessment:
The incident appears to be a multi-stage attack, starting with phishing to steal user credentials, followed by brute-force login attempts, unauthorized access, and privilege escalation. This indicates that the attacker successfully gained control of an administrative account and escalated privileges to root level.

Severity:
High
